"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/654327","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-12-12","<p>Between 2003 and 2005 a total of 55 War Widows remarried and relinquished their War Widow's pensions. Records between 1996 and 2003 are incomplete but where there are records these show that 97 War Widow's pensions were relinquished during that period. The Department holds no relevant records prior to 1996.</p><p>I remain sympathetic to the circumstances of this group of widows and officials continue to consider potential options and expect that the financial and legal position will be clarified in the new year. The potential options are being dealt with by the policy team that has responsibility for compensation schemes.</p><p>Recent meetings on the subject of reinstatement of War Widow's pensions have included my meeting with Mrs Wills BEM, Chairman of the War Widow's Association of Great Britain, and with the hon. Member for Leeds North West (Mr Mulholland). Officials, on my behalf, met with the South East Fermanagh Foundation and Ulster Defence Regiment widows to discuss this issue.</p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/654327/answer",,,,,"56546 ; 56547","2016-12-12T17:39:46.43Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/654327/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/654327/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-12-07","War Widows: Compensation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what the timescale is for the review of the Government's policy on compensation for war widows who remarried between 1973 and 2005.","false","Biography information for Owen Smith","Pontypridd","Owen Smith","56548"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/654328","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-12-12","<p>The Defence Infrastructure Organisation (DIO) has not reimbursed CarillionAmey for the purchase of any boilers. The replacement of 3,000 boilers has been directly funded by DIO under a capital works life cycle replacement programme and are scheduled for replacement in Service Family Accommodation (SFA) by March 2017. Approximately 1,000 boilers have already been replaced under this programme.</p><p>This is in addition to approximately 1,000 boilers being replaced by CarillionAmey as part of the National Housing Prime contract. Boiler replacement is a core service under this contract and thus will be paid for under the normal contractual arrangements.</p><p>By the end of Financial Year 2016-2017 approximately 5,585 SFA boilers will have been replaced in total under the above works.</p><p>In line with previous years, DIO is monitoring closely the heating situation within SFA during the winter months to ensure any potential problems are identified and resolved quickly.</p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/654328/answer",,,,,,"2016-12-12T17:33:55.697Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/654328/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/654328/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-12-07","CarillionAmey","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, whether the Defence Infrastructure Organisation (DIO) has reimbursed CarillionAmey for the purchase of 3,000 boilers approved by DIO to ensure winter boiler breakdown requirements are met in accordance with key performance indicators; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Anne-Marie Trevelyan","Berwick-upon-Tweed","Mrs Anne-Marie Trevelyan","56549"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/654329","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-12-15","<p>A total of 25 members of the UK Armed Forces and 10 Ministry of Defence civilian staff attended the naming ceremony for RFA TIDERACE.</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/654329/answer",,,,,,"2016-12-15T16:11:24.807Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/654329/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/654329/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-12-07","RFA Tiderace","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many (a) staff of his Department and (b) members of the UK armed forces were in attendance at the naming ceremony for RFA Tiderace at DSME Shipyard in Okpo, South Korea, on 1 December 2016.","false","Biography information for Douglas Chapman","Dunfermline and West Fife","Douglas Chapman","56630"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/654330","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-12-15","<p>We announced in the Strategic Defence and Security Review 2015 that we would improve the availability of our Type 45 Destroyers. As part of the Power Improvement Project for Type 45, the Ministry of Defence is planning to improve system resilience by adding upgraded diesel generators to provide further electrical generation capacity.</p><p>For current cost estimates, I refer the right hon. Member to the answer I gave on 16 September 2016 (to Question 46180) to the hon. Member for Strangford (Mr Shannon).</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/654330/answer","20160916_46180_Type_45_Destroyers.docx","20160916_46180_Type_45_Destroyers.docx","46180 - WQnA extract on Type 45 Destroyers","46180 - WQnA extract on Type 45 Destroyers",,"2016-12-15T16:08:44.39Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/654330/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/654330/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-12-07","Type 45 Destroyers","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what recent estimate he has made of the cost to the public purse of refitting the six Type 45 destroyers with intercoolers capable of operating in warm climates.","false","Biography information for Michael Gove","Surrey Heath","Michael Gove","56621"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/654331","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-12-15","<p>The testing and integration programme for all three weapons remains on track to be delivered in line with the UK F-35B Lightning initial operating capability date of December 2018. The UK has a through-life cost for the F-35, which includes weapons integration testing; this figure cannot be broken out to provide a figure for the weapons integration element. Overall, the UK F-35 programme remains within its cost approval.</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/654331/answer",,,,,,"2016-12-15T16:10:55.7Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/654331/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/654331/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-12-07","Joint Strike Fighter Aircraft","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what the most recent timetable is for the weapons testing programme for the F35B Joint Strike Fighter with the (a) Raytheon Paveway IV, (b) MBDA ASRAAM and (c) MBDA AMRAAM; and if he will estimate the costs of integrating each of those systems.","false","Biography information for Douglas Chapman","Dunfermline and West Fife","Douglas Chapman","56632"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/654332","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-12-15","<p>Our Defence activity in the Gulf directly supports the UK's national security objectives. Our projected spending will be allocated to, amongst other things: our persistent operational presence; a permanent footprint of bases and support facilities across the region; and a significant programme of exercises, training and capacity-building.</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/654332/answer",,,,,,"2016-12-15T16:09:41.973Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/654332/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/654332/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-12-07","Gulf States","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how the £3 billion in defence expenditure in the Gulf Region announced by the Prime Minister during her visit to Bahrain in December 2016 will be allocated.","false","Biography information for Douglas Chapman","Dunfermline and West Fife","Douglas Chapman","56641"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/654333","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-12-12","<p>The Naval Service equivalent tradition of patronage is a Lady Sponsor. The Lady Sponsor for RFA TIDERACE is Mrs Anita Lister.</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/654333/answer",,,,,,"2016-12-12T16:37:43.717Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/654333/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/654333/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-12-07","RFA Tiderace","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, who is the designated patron of RFA Tiderace.","false","Biography information for Douglas Chapman","Dunfermline and West Fife","Douglas Chapman","56629"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/654334","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-12-15","<p>There are no members of the United States Marine Corps seconded to HMS QUEEN ELIZABETH.</p><p> </p><p>HMS QUEEN ELIZABETH now has the largest ship's company in the Royal Navy under the command of Captain Jerry Kyd, and this will continue to grow against a planned profile until summer 2017 as her capability develops.</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/654334/answer",,,,,,"2016-12-15T16:12:29.477Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/654334/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/654334/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-12-07","HMS Queen Elizabeth","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many members of the United States Marine Corps are seconded to HMS Queen Elizabeth.","false","Biography information for Douglas Chapman","Dunfermline and West Fife","Douglas Chapman","56631"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/654335","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-12-15","<p>The ultimate guarantee of our security is provided by our independent nuclear deterrent. In addition, the NATO Ballistic Missile Defence (BMD) network protects the UK and, as set out in the 2015 Strategic Defence and Security Review (SDSR), we will invest in a ground-based BMD radar which will enhance this system. We are investigating the potential of the Royal Navy's Type 45 Destroyer to operate in a BMD role, as also set out in the SDSR.</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/654335/answer",,,,,,"2016-12-15T16:10:18.73Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/654335/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/654335/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-12-07","Ballistic Missile Defence: Warships","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, which ballistic missile defence systems protect the UK; and whether the Government has considered the potential merits of the use of ship-based ballistic missile defence systems.","false","Biography information for Douglas Chapman","Dunfermline and West Fife","Douglas Chapman","56517"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/654336","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-12-13","<p>I refer the hon. Member to the answer given by my hon. Friend the then Minister of State for Defence Procurement (Mr Dunne) on 20 October 2015 to Question 11346.</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/654336/answer","20151020_11346_Tornado_Aircraft.docx","20151020_11346_Tornado_Aircraft.docx","11346 - WQnA extract on Tornado Aircraft","11346 - WQnA extract on Tornado Aircraft",,"2016-12-13T16:33:18.913Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/654336/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/654336/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-12-07","Tornado Aircraft","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what the planned out-of-service date is for the Tornado fast jet fleet.","false","Biography information for Douglas Chapman","Dunfermline and West Fife","Douglas Chapman","56520"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/654337","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-12-14","<p>The UK Airprox Board publish all reports and analysis on their website at https://www.airproxboard.org.uk/home/. For ease of reference the attached table identifies the total number within each category and by geographic area for 2016. There are a number of reports which are unassessed as they remain under-investigation, these are included under category U.</p><p> </p><p>Due to the range of UK military aviation activity that occurs overseas I have also included data on Airprox occurrences involving UK military aircraft operating outside UK Airspace, as assessed by the Military Aviation Authority.</p><p> </p>","Hemel Hempstead","Mike Penning","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/654337/answer","56521 - Airprox Incidents by Category and Location in the Last 12 Months.docx","56521 - Airprox Incidents by Category and Location in the Last 12 Months.docx","56521 - Ministry of Defence Airprox Incidents","56521 - Ministry of Defence Airprox Incidents",,"2016-12-14T16:09:50.96Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/654337/answer","Biography information for Sir Mike Penning","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/654337/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-12-07","Military Aircraft: Air Misses","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many airprox incidents there have been by (a) category and (b) location in the last 12 months.","false","Biography information for Douglas Chapman","Dunfermline and West Fife","Douglas Chapman","56521"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/654338","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-12-14","<p>The Government of the United Kingdom would strongly condemn any desecration of any site of maritime military graves. By invoking the principle of Sovereign Immunity, and by designating specific vessels under the Protection of Wrecks Act 1973 and the Protection of Maritime Remains Act 1986, we endeavour to protect these important sites where we are able.</p><p> </p><p>Where we have evidence of desecration of the wrecks of Royal Navy vessels, we will take appropriate action, including working with regional Governments and partners to prevent inappropriate activity at such sites. It should be appreciated however that, given the vast locations of Royal Navy wrecks around the world, that there are limitations on what protection we can provide.</p><p> </p><p>The Department became aware of the possible illegal salvage of items from HMS Exeter, Encounter and Electra on 8 November 2016.</p><p> </p><p>As is appropriate, Foreign and Commonwealth Office officials have been in contact with the Indonesian Government, expressing our serious concerns and requesting that the reports are fully investigated.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","Hemel Hempstead","Mike Penning","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/654338/answer",,,,,"56523 ; 56524","2016-12-14T16:10:41.807Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/654338/answer","Biography information for Sir Mike Penning","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/654338/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-12-07","Warships: Wrecks","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, on what date his Department learned of the disappearance of HMS (a) Exeter, (b) Encounter and (c) Electra.","false","Biography information for Dr Matthew Offord","Hendon","Dr Matthew Offord","56522"
