"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/654414","Department of Health","false","2016-12-12","<p>Malnutrition can be caused by a variety of factors, including an inability to absorb nutrients normally, or a condition or disease which affects a patient’s ability to feed normally. The hospital bed days for finished consultant episodes with primary diagnosis of malnutrition and a secondary diagnosis of dementia in each of the last 10 years is presented in the following table.</p><table><tbody><tr><td><p>Year</p></td><td><p>Bed Days</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2006-07</p></td><td><p>604</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2007-08</p></td><td><p>363</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2008-09</p></td><td><p>568</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2009-10</p></td><td><p>667</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2010-11</p></td><td><p>375</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2011-12</p></td><td><p>1,137</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2012-13</p></td><td><p>1,186</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2013-14</p></td><td><p>850</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2014-15</p></td><td><p>836</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2015-16</p></td><td><p>1,082</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p>","Oxford West and Abingdon","Nicola Blackwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/654414/answer",,,,,,"2016-12-12T16:37:54.93Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/654414/answer","Biography information for Baroness Blackwood of North Oxford","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/654414/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2016-12-07","Dementia and Malnutrition","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, how many hospital bed days there were for people with a primary diagnosis of malnutrition and a secondary diagnosis of dementia in each of the last 10 years.","false","Biography information for Jonathan Ashworth","Leicester South","Jonathan Ashworth","56654"
